Schooling has been disrupted for a second day at Opelweg Primary in Eden Park on Gauteng’s East Rand. On Monday night the School Governing Body (SGB) and the education department failed to reach an agreement. Parents claim a rogue group of teachers is rendering the school ungovernable. They are seemingly unfazed about their children’s education being compromised. They want the deputy principal and some educators removed. Struggle Stalwart, Solly Peterson says, Gauteng Education has condemned the disruption, while the parties seek a solution. Learners bear the brunt of factional battles. CLICK LINK FOR MORE:  